@startuml 03-genesis-flow-updated
title Genesis Flow (First-Time Setup)

skinparam backgroundColor #FEFEFE
skinparam roundcorner 10
skinparam shadowing false

|User|
start
:Enter Master Password;
:Confirm Master Password;

|Extension|
:Validate Password Strength;
note right
    - Minimum entropy check
    - HIBP Pwned check (k-anonymity)
    - Reject weak passwords
end note

if (Password Strong?) then (yes)
else (no)
    :Show Strength Warning;
    stop
endif

|WebCrypto|
:Generate Random Salt (32 bytes);
:Generate Device ID (UUID v4);
:Generate Vault Key (256-bit random);
:Generate Device Signing Key (Ed25519);
:Generate Device Exchange Key (ECDH P-256);

|Extension|
:Derive Master KEK;
note right
    PBKDF2(SHA256(pwd + pepper), salt, 600k)
end note

:Wrap Device Private Keys with Master KEK;

|User|
split
   :Choose **Master Password** Backup;
   |Extension|
   :Create Master Backup Slot;
   note right
       Type: "master"
       Alg: PBKDF2+AESKW
       KEK derived from Password
   end note
split again
   :Choose **Recovery Key** Backup;
   |WebCrypto|
   :Generate 256-bit Random Recovery Key;
   |User|
   :Save/Write Down Recovery Key;
   :Confirm Recovery Key (Validation);
   |Extension|
   :Create Recovery Slot;
   note right
       Type: "recovery-key"
       Alg: AESKW
       KEK is the Recovery Key
   end note
end split

|Extension|
:Create Empty Vault;
:Encrypt Vault with Vault Key;
:Sign Envelope (Ed25519);

|IndexedDB|
:Store Wrapped Device Keys;
:Store Salt, Device ID, and Encrypted Vault;

|Extension|
:secureWipe(passwordBuffer & recoveryKeyBuffer);
:Mark Setup Complete;

|User|
:Redirect to Unlock Screen;
stop

legend right
    **Security Note:**
    - Recovery Key is NEVER stored.
    - All sensitive buffers are wiped.
    - Non-extractable keys in RAM.
endlegend

@enduml